<subSubSection pageId="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1302,1327]" pageId="8">Comments.</emphasis>
Initially, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamanini" box="[441,628,1302,1327]" pageId="8" refString="Tamanini, L. (1951) Terzo contributo allo studio del genere Velia Latr. (Hemipt. - Heteropt., Veliidae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 26 (366) [1949], 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1951">
Tamanini (
<number box="[562,620,1302,1327]" pageId="8" value="1951.0">1951</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[748,858,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serbica">
<emphasis box="[748,761,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[775,858,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="8">serbica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1156,1302,1327]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saulii">
<emphasis box="[1068,1082,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1094,1156,1302,1327]" italics="true" pageId="8">saulii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single female specimen. Later he included it in the 
<taxonomicName box="[594,695,1339,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[594,607,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[625,695,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8">affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and redescribed it as 
<taxonomicName box="[1034,1257,1338,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mancinii" subSpecies="serbica">
<emphasis box="[1034,1047,1340,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1066,1257,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="8">mancinii serbica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on male specimens originating from Pirin, 
<collectingCountry box="[535,632,1374,1399]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="8">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tamanini" box="[646,821,1374,1399]" pageId="8" refString="Tamanini, L. (1959) Valore tassonomico della Velia serbica Tam. e brevi osservazioni sulle Velia della Bulgaria (Hem. Heter., Veliadae). Atti della Accademia Roveretana degli Agiati, 6 (1957), 131 - 135." type="journal article" year="1959">
Tamanini 
<number box="[761,821,1374,1399]" pageId="8" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Finally, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamanini" box="[933,1120,1374,1399]" pageId="8" refString="Tamanini, L. (1971) Osservazioni sulle Velia serbica Tam., V. hoberlandti Tam., V. eckerleini Tam. e descrizione di una nuova specie. (Heteroptera Veliidae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 103, 30 - 35." type="journal article" year="1971">
Tamanini (
<number box="[1054,1112,1375,1399]" pageId="8" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
argued for its species status after he found both 
<taxonomicName box="[408,542,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mancinii">
<emphasis box="[408,421,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[444,542,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="8">mancinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[615,735,1410,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serbica">
<emphasis box="[615,628,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[652,735,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="8">serbica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
co-occurring in Jabolnica, 
<collectingCountry box="[1076,1373,1410,1435]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="8">Bosnia and Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
. The macropterous specimens of this species has never been recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,762,1723]" pageId="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1482,1507]" pageId="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,467,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serbica">
<emphasis box="[322,467,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="8">Velia serbica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in small streams, in shaded places, in south-western 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1250,1482,1507]" name="Romania" pageId="8">Romania</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1292,1483,1507]" name="American Samoa" pageId="8">As</collectingCountry>
presented in 
<figureCitation box="[151,218,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1131,1153]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,193,1107]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,193,1110]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution of Velia affinis filippii Tamanini, 1947 (rhombus), Velia caprai caprai Tamanini, 1947 (square), Velia mancinii mancinii Tamanini, 1947 (triangle), Velia saulii Tamanini, 1947 (dot) and Velia serbica Tamanini, 1951 (star) in Romania. Solid shapes represent published records while blank shapes represent records from this study." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234008/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[202,218,1519,1543]" pageId="8" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
, its distribution is confined between the Mureș River in the north and Strei and Jiu Rivers in the east. We did not find it coexisting with other 
<emphasis box="[514,567,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="8">Vel ia</emphasis>
species, but in the Cerna Valley we observed that in some cases on the same stream at lower altitudes 
<taxonomicName box="[429,539,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serbica">
<emphasis box="[429,442,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[456,539,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="8">serbica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present, whilst upstream it is replaced by 
<taxonomicName box="[1030,1259,1591,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Velia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="mancinii" subSpecies="mancinii">
<emphasis box="[1030,1043,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="8">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1057,1259,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="8">mancinii mancinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most probably they may cohabit, as also mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamanini" box="[596,786,1626,1651]" pageId="8" refString="Tamanini, L. (1971) Osservazioni sulle Velia serbica Tam., V. hoberlandti Tam., V. eckerleini Tam. e descrizione di una nuova specie. (Heteroptera Veliidae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 103, 30 - 35." type="journal article" year="1971">
Tamanini (
<number box="[716,776,1627,1651]" pageId="8" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The altitudes vary between 
<number box="[1102,1144,1627,1651]" pageId="8" value="170.0">170</number>
and 
<quantity box="[1197,1282,1627,1651]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3699999999999999" pageId="8" unit="m" value="1370.0">1370 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<figureCitation box="[1354,1422,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1205,1227]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,560,1176]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,553,1184]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Boxplots representing the altitudinal ranges of Veliidae in Romania." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234010/files/figure.png" pageId="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1406,1422,1626,1651]" pageId="8" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
